</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF80FF9BF3C7FD1EED64FD35" box="[721,852,692,719]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStart-3="Fig" captionStart-4="Fig" captionStart-5="Fig" captionStartId-0="5.[171,204,1732,1754]" captionStartId-1="1.[178,211,875,897]" captionStartId-2="2.[168,201,1145,1167]" captionStartId-3="3.[174,207,1718,1740]" captionStartId-4="4.[166,199,1722,1744]" captionStartId-5="6.[170,202,1708,1730]" captionTargetBox-0="[321,1089,843,1706]" captionTargetBox-1="[273,1126,188,832]" captionTargetBox-2="[258,1095,178,1094]" captionTargetBox-3="[263,1124,733,1688]" captionTargetBox-4="[275,1082,1029,1703]" captionTargetBox-5="[296,1099,565,1690]" captionTargetId-0="figure-5@5.[311,1097,833,1721]" captionTargetId-1="figure-316@1.[254,1139,174,852]" captionTargetId-2="figure-247@2.[235,1130,166,1111]" captionTargetId-3="figure-5@3.[237,1132,714,1714]" captionTargetId-4="figure-329@4.[256,1104,1015,1723]" captionTargetId-5="figure-130@6.[288,1111,557,1687]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="1" captionTargetPageId-2="2" captionTargetPageId-3="3" captionTargetPageId-4="4" captionText-0="Fig. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E.plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — antenna; 2, 8 — mesonotum; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E. plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — усик; 2, 8 — среднеспинка; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-1="Fig. 1. Adialytus salicaphis, ♀ (1–5) and A. ambiguus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — antenna; 2, 7 — forewing; 3, 8 — propodeum; 4, 9 — petiole; 5, 10 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 1. Adialytus salicaphis, ♀ (1–5) и A. ambiguus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — усик; 2, 7 — переднее крыло; 3, 8 — проподеум; 4, 9 — стебелёк; 5, 10 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-2="Fig. 2. Aphidius megourae, ♀ (1–6) and A. funebris, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — head, dorsal aspect; 2, 8 — antenna; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 2. Aphidius megourae, ♀ (1–6) и A. funebris, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — голова, вид сверху; 2, 8 — усик; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-3="Fig. 3. Areopraon silvestre, ♀ (1–6) and Praon volucre, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — antenna; 2, 8 — mesonotum; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 3. Areopraon silvestre, ♀ (1–6) и Praon volucre, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — усик; 2, 8 — среднеспинка; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-4="Fig. 4. Diaeretus leucopterus, ♀ (1–5) and Diaeretiella rapae, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — antenna; 2, 7 — forewing; 3, 8 — propodeum; 4, 9 — petiole; 5, 10 — ovipositor sheath (5 — after Takada, 1968). Рис. 4. Diaeretus leucopterus, ♀ (1–5) и Diaeretiella rapae, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — усик; 2, 7 — переднее крыло; 3, 8 — проподеум; 4, 9 — стебелёк; 5, 10 — створки яйцеклада (5 — по: Takada, 1968)." captionText-5="Fig.6. Paralipsis enervis, ♀ (1–7) and Protaphidius wissmannii,♀ (9–12, 14), Ơ (8, 13): 1, 8 — habitus; 2, 9 — head, lateral aspect; 3, 10 — antenna; 4, 11 — forewing; 5, 12 — propodeum; 6, 13 — petiole; 7, 14 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 6. Paralipsis enervis, ♀ (1–7) и Protaphidius wissmannii, ♀ (9–12, 14), Ơ (8, 13): 1, 8 — габитус; 2, 9 — голова, вид сбоку; 3, 10 — усик; 4, 11 — переднее крыло; 5, 12 — проподеум; 6, 13 — стебелёк; 7, 14 — створки яйцеклада." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467462" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467454" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449135" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467456" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467460" figureDoi-5="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467466" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6467462/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6467454/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6449135/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6467456/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6467460/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/6467466/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">
fig. 5, 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF80FF9BF23EFD1EED64FD35" box="[808,852,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">1–6</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) differs from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF80FF9BF548FD1EEF35FD15" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF80FF9BF548FD1EEAE0FD35" box="[1118,1232,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">Ephedrus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the mesoscutum slightly wider than long (
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF80FF9BF243FD7EEDAAFD14" box="[853,922,724,751]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[171,204,1732,1754]" captionTargetBox="[321,1089,843,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[311,1097,833,1721]" captionText="Fig. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E.plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — antenna; 2, 8 — mesonotum; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E. plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — усик; 2, 8 — среднеспинка; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6467462/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF80FF9BF2BCFD7FED88FD14" box="[938,952,725,751]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">2</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF80FF9BF2DDFD7FEDE9FD14" box="[971,985,725,751]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">8</emphasis>
); from 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF80FF9BF529FD7FEAE0FD15" baseAuthorityName="Nees" baseAuthorityYear="1811" box="[1087,1232,724,750]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Ephedrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagiator">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF80FF9BF529FD7FEAE0FD15" box="[1087,1232,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">E. plagiator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF80FF9BF1A1FD5EEECBFCF4" box="[183,251,756,783]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[171,204,1732,1754]" captionTargetBox="[321,1089,843,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[311,1097,833,1721]" captionText="Fig. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E.plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — antenna; 2, 8 — mesonotum; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E. plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — усик; 2, 8 — среднеспинка; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6467462/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF80FF9BF01DFD5FEF46FCF4" box="[267,374,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">
7, 
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF80FF9BF03DFD5FEF78FCF4" box="[299,328,757,783]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[172,205,1714,1736]" captionTargetBox="[256,1150,742,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-11@10.[253,1162,742,1695]" captionText="Fig. 10. Trioxys curvicaudus, ♀ (1–5) and Trioxys pallidus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — antenna; 2, 7 — forewing; 3, 8 — propodeum; 4, 9 — petiole; 5 a, 5 b, 10 — ovipositor sheath and prongs. Рис. 10. Trioxys curvicaudus, ♀ (1–5) и Trioxys pallidus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — усик; 2, 7 — переднее крыло; 3, 8 — проподеум; 4, 9 — стебелёк; 5 a, 5 b, 10 — створки яйцеклада и пронги." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6467470/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="392">10</figureCitation>
–12
</emphasis>
) it differs by: 1) length ratio of F1/F2 is bigger and equals 1.2–1.3; 2) F1 is yellow, without or with 1 longitudinal placode; 3) shorter 2nd submarginal cell of forewing; 4) wider central areola on propodeum; 5) shorter petiole with more prominent spiracular tubercules; 5) shorter ovipositor sheath with straighter margin of apex. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF83FF98F006FEBAEF97FED2" authorityName="Stary" authorityYear="1962" box="[272,423,271,297]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Ephedrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerasicola">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF83FF98F006FEBAEF97FED2" box="[272,423,271,297]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="393">E. cerasicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forewing veins (
<collectingRegion id="49BD69A0FF83FF98F361FEA5ECACFED1" box="[631,668,271,298]" country="Bulgaria" name="Ruse" pageId="6" pageNumber="393">RS</collectingRegion>
+M)a and 2 
